109	// Global error handler.
110	//
111	// AppError is the structured error path — pass message + code through.
112	// Anything else is an unhandled exception. We log it through the
113	// system logger with the traceId so support can correlate, but in
114	// production we strip the stack and the raw error message from both
115	// the log line and the response body. This avoids leaking SQL
116	// fragments, file paths, secrets that may have ended up inside an
117	// exception message, or stack traces that disclose internals.
118	//
119	// In non-production we keep the full stack so developers can debug.
120	//
